    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT9-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">talaimakaṟkut tōḻi vāyil nērntatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The confidante granting the door/mediation to HIM.</p>
          </div>

        <div xml:id="KT9">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                yāyā kiyaḷē māa yōḷē</l>
<l>                maṭaimāṇ ceppiṟ ṟamiya vaikiya</l>
<l>                peyyāp pūviṉ meycā yiṉaḷē</l>
<l>                pācaṭai nivanta kaṇaikkā ṉeyta</l>
<l>                liṉamī ṉiruṅkaḻi yōta malkutoṟuṅ</l>
<l>                kayamūḻku makaḷir kaṇṇiṉ māṉun</l>
<l>                taṇṇan tuṟaivaṉ koṭumai</l>
<l>                nammu ṇāṇik karappā ṭummē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>She is [now] mother<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">yāy</term> "mother" in this connection is interpreted by TVG as the person who feels responsible for the integrity and honour of her house and who accordingly wishes to keep secret HIS escapades – an appealing sense for a rather enigmatic phrase. Though taking it literal should also be considered: since SHE has become mother, HE has an even transcultural reason for going astray.</note>, the dark one!</l>
<l>Like a flower kept alone in a vessel famed for<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">maṭai māṇ</term> is explained by TVG as <q>tight clasp</q>, but that does not fit the context any better, and the word order should rather be <term xml:lang="ta">māṇ maṭai</term>.</note> its clasp,</l>
<l>unworn, her body is emaciated.</l>
<l>Ashamed among us she plays hiding<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">āṭum</term>: the choice of habitual future emphasises the durative character of the action; one is tempted to translate <q>she usually plays over</q>.</note></l>
<l rend="indent">the faithlessness of the man from the cool ghat</l>
<l rend="indent">where the round-stemmed blue waterlilies risen up from green leaves</l>
<l rend="indent">whenever the flood rises in the dark backwaters with various fish<note place="foot">TVG sees <term xml:lang="ta">iṉam mīṉ</term> as <q>varieties of fish</q>. This might be an explanation for the unusual positioning (contrary to <term xml:lang="ta">mīṉ iṉam</term> <q>fish swarm</q>, i.e. many of one sort).</note></l>
<l rend="indent">resemble the eyes of women diving in tanks.</l>
             </lg>
        </div>
